tation was attempted earlier based on lottery per individual clerics and it didn't work.  Why it didn't work is not important.<br>
<br>
I am in the mood for tossing out ideas, however.  I am not a cleric, but I did participate in the old SolB camp once for my roomate.  He followed in a Naggy raid to get into the camp.  Naggy went down, he stuck around for Rage.  Every 8 hours a guild group showed up to knock down the FG's.  I participated in two of those beat downs, including one where we didn't have a tank, and our group was only 4 members.  My roomie stayed online from the day of that Naggy raid, through TWO Ragefires (him getting the second).  The account was passed among people that could be online.  During the time he was online, he was visited by various members of other guilds, who not only wished him luck, but also hoped he would go LD or crash or die or whatever, thus claiming the camp.  During the final night before Rage popped, I took a stint at his PC while he slept for the first solid time in a week.<br>
<br>
Clearly this is not the way to go.  However, the current FFA solution is also not the way to go.  In the end it only hurts long standing guilds that have been around for years.  Having a GM intervene is also not the prefered way of doing things.<br>
<br>
A rotation only works if people respect the rotation, much like a camp only works if people respect the camp.  Right now we have everyone respecting nothing.  This camp is the focal point of destroying a community that for as long as I have been a part of, has allowed even the smallest of players to participate on raids regardless of guild affiliation (pick up raids).<br>
<br>
I propose this... chew it up and toss it back in my face if ya like:<br>
<br>
1.  Put Ragefire on a weekly rotation among guilds.<br>
2.  Each guild (or group of guilds) is on the rotation for a period of one week's time.<br>
3.  During that time, the guild on rotation must maintain a presence in Skyfire.  What constitutes a presense can be hatched out, however IMHO one group should be fine.<br>
4.  During the week the guild is on rotation, all Ragefire spawns are defaulted to that guild, provided<br>
-They have a cleric for every spawn of Ragefire.<br>
-The cleric must be at the Ragefire stage.<br>
-The guild is capable of killing Ragefire within 24 hours of spawn.<br>
5.  For purposes of this rotation, guilds can team up and take one slot in the rotation.  Guilds cannot team up multiple times to be included in multiple slots.  This will allow small guilds to participate.<br>
6.  If for any reason Ragefire is NOT dead 24 hours after spawn, he becomes FFA for THAT SPAWN ONLY.  This can also be discussed.<br>
<br>
Clearly there are alot of holes in the above proposal.  For one, the rotation being weekly could be months.  For another, all it takes is one guild who decides not to respect the rotation to kill the whole thing.  Also, unguilded clerics are not included in the above scenarios.<br>
<br>
A guild could also be the recipient of bad luck.  Patch Sunday, no spawn, patch Tuesday, still no spawn, patch Thursday, still no spawn.  On the other hand, a guild could get 3 ragefires in one week.<br>
<br>
I would be willing to help organize this, run the rotation, etc.  As a shaman, I have no vested interest in the mob.  As a guild officer, I do have a vested interest in resolution to the matter.  In any case, we as a community need to come up with something that a large majority of folks will agree too.<br>
<br>
As always, constructive criticism is welcome. <p>Tanuden <BR>
